import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="region", y="income", data=data, palette="Set3")
    ax.set_title("What is the distribution of income across different regions?")
    ax.set_xlabel("Region")
    ax.set_ylabel("Income")
    ax.axhline(y=data['income'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Income: {:.2f}'.format(data['income'].median()))
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('region').mean().reset_index()
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='region', y='income', data=data, color='blue', label='Income')
    sns.barplot(x='region', y='health', data=data, color='red', label='Health')
    ax.set_xlabel('Region')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average')
    ax.set_title('What is the average income and health of each region?')
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
